Introduction

	pBurst is an Internet Relay Chat Protocol Burster and debugger for IRC
	server to server protocol. It's designed to assist developers of IRC 
        services and daemon in their ability to code efficient and stable 
        packages.

Installation

	Step 1 (compiling)

	Perform the following unix commands:

	./configure
	make install
	mkdir logs
	cp etc/example.conf etc/pburst.conf

	Step 2 (configuring)

	Edit etc/pburst.conf with your favorite text editor, pico is usually
        a good choice but for you die hards I guess vi will work.

	Step 3 (running)

	Perform the following unix commands:

	./pBurst -c etc/pburst.conf

	Once pBurst is run you may type /HELP at any time for a list of
	available commands.

